@startuml
title TestForge — Sequência: Data-Driven Testing (massa externa JSON)

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 12

actor "QA" as QA
participant "CLI\n(compile --data)" as CLI
participant "Recording\nNormalizer" as NORM
participant "Data\nExtractor" as DE
database "recordings/\n(raw_events.jsonl)" as REC
participant "Compiler\nPlaywright" as COMP
database "test_data.json\n(massa externa)" as TDATA
database "semantic_tests/\n(script.py)" as SCRIPT
participant "Runner\nInline" as RUN
participant "Browser\n(Playwright)" as BROWSER

== 1. Extração da Massa de Dados ==

CLI -> NORM: normalize(rec_dir) → SemanticTestCase
NORM -> REC: le raw_events.jsonl
NORM --> CLI: 46 steps

CLI -> DE: extract_test_data(rec_dir)
DE -> REC: le raw_events.jsonl

loop cada evento fill
  DE -> DE: extrai value + target.label/placeholder
  DE -> DE: nomeia campo: "cpf", "nome"...
  DE -> DE: deduplica (mesmo nome+valor)
  DE -> DE: detecta sensivel (CPF, senha) → alerta
end

DE -> TDATA: {\n  "fields": {\n    "cpf": "12345678900"\n  },\n  "sensitive_alerts": [...]\n}

CLI -> CLI: ⚠ Sensitive: cpf — alert_only

== 2. Compilação Data-Driven ==

CLI -> COMP: compile(stc, data_file="test_data.json")

COMP -> COMP: gera script com:\nimport json, os\n_data = json.load(open("test_data.json"))

loop cada step fill
  COMP -> COMP: resolve valor:\n_data.get("cpf", "12345678900")
  note right: Se JSON existe → usa valor externo\nSe JSON ausente → fallback hardcoded
end

COMP -> SCRIPT: test_st_fluxo.py

== 3. Execução com Massa Externa ==

QA -> RUN: testforge run script.py
RUN -> BROWSER: page.goto(url)

loop cada step fill
  RUN -> RUN: le valor do step
  RUN -> SCRIPT: _data.get("cpf", "12345678900")
  RUN -> TDATA: le test_data.json
  TDATA --> RUN: "cpf": "12345678900"
  RUN -> BROWSER: page.fill(sel, "12345678900")
end

== 4. Alteração de Massa (sem recompilar) ==

QA -> TDATA: edita JSON:\n"cpf": "99988877766"

QA -> RUN: testforge run script.py
RUN -> TDATA: le test_data.json
TDATA --> RUN: "cpf": "99988877766"
RUN -> BROWSER: page.fill(sel, "99988877766")
note right: Mesmo script, dados diferentes\nSem recompilar!

== 5. Múltiplos Cenários (--scenarios) ==

QA -> CLI: compile "fluxo" --data --scenarios

DE -> TDATA: {\n  "scenarios": {\n    "default": {"cpf": "123"},\n    "cpf_invalido": {"cpf": "000"}\n  }\n}

note over TDATA: Script lê _data["scenarios"]["default"]\nPode testar múltiplos cenários

@enduml
